com.intuit.wasabi.tests.service

Class IntegrationExperiment

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intuit.wasabi.tests.library.ServiceTestBase
      • com.intuit.wasabi.tests.library.TestBase
        • com.intuit.wasabi.tests.service.IntegrationExperiment

  • public class IntegrationExperiment
extends TestBase
    Tests the experiment functionality. Known Issues: - The python test checked for the number of experiments, but since this could be run on production environments it does not feel right to check those numbers, as they might change by other accessors. These transitions are tested: (row transitions to column) 
     DR = DRAFT, R = RUNNING, P = PAUSED, DEL = DELETED, T = TERMINATED, I = INVALID
 
     -> |DR | R | P |DEL| T | I |
 ---+---+---+---+---+---+---+
 DR | b | bc| c | r | r | b |
 R  | b | b | b | b | c | b |
 P  | b | b | b | b | b | b |
 DEL| b | b | b | b | b | b |
 T  | b | b | b | b | b | b |
 I  | x | x | x | x | x | x |
    Table legend:
    • x: not possible
    • o: not covered
    • b: covered by t_basicStateTransitions(String, int)
    • c: covered by t_complexStateTransitions()
    • r: covered by t_remainingTransitionTests()

        public void t_complexStateTransitions()
        Tests different experiment state transitions with other constraints like too few buckets. The transitions tested are: DR -> R -> T Each with 0 buckets, buckets with fewer than 100% allocation and the correct amount of buckets with allocations.
